    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Take your chicken out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-hunters-chicken-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-greens/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken </strong>to the<strong> </strong>middle of the 2 pieces of <strong>tin foil </strong>(doubling it up prevents any leakages!) then loosely scrunch the edges of the <strong>tin foil</strong> around the chicken leaving the top exposed</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken</strong> to a tray (or two!)</p><p>Drizzle with<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 8-10 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-hunters-chicken-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-greens/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat and bring to the boil</p><p>Cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain, return them to the pot and cover to keep warm</p><p>Wash your <strong>spring greens</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper, rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-hunters-chicken-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-greens/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced spring greens </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) with a generous splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter, </strong>scrunch the foil around the spring greens to form a tightly sealed parcel</p><p>After the chicken has had 8-10 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the tin foil parcel[s] to the other side of the tray[s]</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 10-12 min or until the spring greens are tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-hunters-chicken-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-greens/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>lighter cheese</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>BBQ sauce </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in a small bowl with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>water</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>hunters sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-hunters-chicken-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-greens/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is nearly ready, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the <strong>cooked potato</strong> and mash until smooth</p><p>Tip: If the mash has cooled down, warm it through over a low heat, stirring constantly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-hunters-chicken-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-greens/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, remove the tray[s] from the oven and spoon most of the <strong>hunters sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) over the <strong>chicken </strong>and sprinkle with the <strong>grated lighter cheese</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 2-3 min or until the cheese is melted \u2013 this is your <strong>hunters chicken </strong>and <strong>garlicky greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-hunters-chicken-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-greens/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>hunters chicken </strong>with the <strong>potato mash </strong>and <strong>garlicky greens </strong>to the side</p><p>Spoon the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>hunters</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> over the <strong>chicken </strong>and finish with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
